1933// Convert camera sample to ARGB with cropping, rotation and vertical flip.
1934// "sample_size" is needed to parse MJPG.
1935// "dst_stride_argb" number of bytes in a row of the dst_argb plane.
1936// Normally this would be the same as dst_width, with recommended alignment
1937// to 16 bytes for better efficiency.
1938// If rotation of 90 or 270 is used, stride is affected. The caller should
1939// allocate the I420 buffer according to rotation.
1940// "dst_stride_u" number of bytes in a row of the dst_u plane.
1941// Normally this would be the same as (dst_width + 1) / 2, with
1942// recommended alignment to 16 bytes for better efficiency.
1943// If rotation of 90 or 270 is used, stride is affected.
1944// "crop_x" and "crop_y" are starting position for cropping.
1945// To center, crop_x = (src_width - dst_width) / 2
1946// crop_y = (src_height - dst_height) / 2
1947// "src_width" / "src_height" is size of src_frame in pixels.
1948// "src_height" can be negative indicating a vertically flipped image source.
1949// "crop_width" / "crop_height" is the size to crop the src to.
1950// Must be less than or equal to src_width/src_height
1951// Cropping parameters are pre-rotation.
1952// "rotation" can be 0, 90, 180 or 270.
1953// "fourcc" is a fourcc. ie 'I420', 'YUY2'
1954// Returns 0 for successful; -1 for invalid parameter. Non-zero for failure.
1955LIBYUV_API
1956int ConvertToARGB(const uint8_t* sample,
1957 size_t sample_size,
1958 uint8_t* dst_argb,
1959 int dst_stride_argb,
1960 int crop_x,
1961 int crop_y,
1962 int src_width,
1963 int src_height,
1964 int crop_width,
1965 int crop_height,
1966 enum RotationMode rotation,
1967 uint32_t fourcc);
